Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
96-100 Grote Street is a key part of the Chinatown Precinct in SA located directly opposite the Lions at the northern end of Moonta Street. With constantly active nightlife, plentiful street parking, and access to the main thoroughfares through the Adelaide CBD there is a lot on offer here for investors looking to secure a significant Adelaide holding.

This 767sqm* space is tenanted by Tangritah Uyghur Restaurant and Star Academy Dance Studio paying $159,457* net per annum. With strong holding income already in place 96-100 Grote Street is an ideal investment for groups looking for future flexibility.  

With the upcoming Market Square redevelopment just across the road, there will be a huge uplift to the local area with a modern quality office space, retail market ‘hub’ and a hotel and apartment offering all in the one spot. The $400,000,000 price tag will be sure to have run-on affects to the immediate area and we expect 96-100 Grote Street will see benefit. 

Key investment highlights include:
- Multi tenanted Chinatown investment
- Estimated net rental of $159,457*
- 1,450sqm* corner site 
- 8* on site car parks
- Capital City zoning for 53meters
- Perfectly positioned near the planned ‘Market Square’ redevelopment
- Expansion opportunities in current tenancy mix

The CBRE Metropolitan Investment and Hotels team are proud to present for sale the business and freehold of the Waikerie Golf and Country Club. The golf course is one of the leading South Australian Riverland courses, boasting a full 18-hole par 72 golf course which is exceptionally curated and offers enjoyment and challenge to both an amateur and experienced golfer.

The key feature of the property however is the 12-room luxury accommodation that has recently been constructed. This is one of the key differences to other regional courses and is proving highly effective for the club and business and attendance which is demonstrated by the pre-booking all the way through to November (with more bookings taken weekly!). 

The course is surrounded by a range of additional vacant sites which the vendor will consider in the divestment which will give the incoming purchaser the opportunity to further expand their operation in time to come.

The key sales highlights include:
- Full par 72 golf course
- 12 suite luxury accommodation
- Range of additional land options available
- Business and freehold being sold
- Impressive net profit through COVID in FY20/21
- 90 Megalitres of recycled water

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing at 4pm (ACST) on the 23rd of September. 

Please contact Harry (0421 747 442) or Ned (0448 689 573) to discuss viewing the financial information for the Waikerie Golf & Country Club from FY20/21.
